nd a Dash of Sass\n|\nWe seek out other people to fight off the loneliness but it's like we're children playing at pretend. We are alone in everything we do, Livy. Alone but not without company.\n\n- Shari Arnold, Neverland\n|\nIn any situation, I ask “What can I do for myself”.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nDiscouragement is your enemy, therefore resist it\n\n- Sunday\n|\nJust reviewing this list, these to-dos and dones, her pace quickens; she feels lighter, she feels smarter, she feels in control, she feels alive.\n\n- Rumaan Alam, Rich and Pretty\n|\nBut inside loss there can be gain, too,like the small silver spider Bela had discovered one dewy morning, curled asleep at the center of a rose.\n\n- Chitra Banerjee Divakaruni, Before We Visit the Goddess\n|\nLord Chi Wen thought three times before taking any action. When the Master heard this, he said: Twice is plenty enough.\n\n- Confucius, The Analects\n|\nIn order to succeed, your desire for success should be greater than your fear of failure.\n\n- Bill\n|\nIn the densest places of man, humanity most easily breaks down\n\n- Pierce Brown, Red Rising\n|\nThe basis, the corner-stone of this Government, was the perfect equality of the free, sovereign, and independent States which made it.\n\n- Robert\n|\nSome pains are physical, and some pains are mental, but the one that's both is dental.\n\n- Ogden\n|\nAs surely as wherever the darkness is not, there you will find the light; wherever the ego is not, there you will find the soul.\n\n- Jennifer Sweete, Dear Sandy - The letter that wrote itself into a Book\n|\nSunglasses are best invention of this worldThey hide eyes,which speak more then words\n\n- Mohammed Zaki Ansari, 'Zaki's Gift Of Love'\n|\nMy maid never sweeps under the bed so I asked her to do so today. Found a pen, three pairs of shoes and the man I had lost two years ago.\n\n- Sanhita\n|\nAs I wrote, I found that Aibileen had some things to say that really weren't in her character. She